data.title: Iran 04 (1966) PDF
data.meta_description: Iran 04 (1966).pdf - Free ebook download as PDF File (.pdf), Text File (.txt) or read book online for free. This document is the contents page and introduction for Volume IV of the Journal of the British Institute of Persian Studies from 1966. It lists the articles contained in the volume, including pieces on Seljuk tomb towers in Iran, inscriptions from mausoleums, mammalian remains from a cave in Iran, and the walls of a place called Tammisha. It also provides information about the governing council and officers of the British Institute of Persian Studies, including its director based in Tehran, Iran. The introduction states that the Institute has an establishment in Tehran where British scholars can reside and discuss subjects of mutual interest with Iranian colleagues, such as archaeology, history, literature, and religion.
